14 def findByType(browser, ident, type):
15  if type != 'css' and type != 'xpath' and type != 'tag' and type != 'id' and type != 'text' and type != 'name' and type != 'href':
16  error = "Improper search method " + str(type)
17  self.assertTrue(False, error)
18  if(type == 'css'):
19  return browser.find_by_css(ident)
20  elif(type == 'xpath'):
21  return browser.find_by_xpath(ident)
22  elif(type == 'tag'):
23  return browser.find_by_tag(ident)
24  elif(type == 'text'):
25  return browser.find_by_text(ident)
26  elif(type == 'id'):
27  return browser.find_by_id(ident)
28  elif(type == 'name'):
29  return browser.find_by_name(ident)
30  elif(type == 'href'):
31  return browser.find_link_by_href(ident)
32  return

55  def clickMenuLink(self, ident, interval=0.1, maxTime=1.0, type='css'):
56  """Searches for an identifier and clicks it. Search method is provided by 'type' argument
57  - either css, xpath, tag, text, id, href or name."""
58  counter = 0.0
59  link = None
60  while counter < maxTime and link is None:
61  try:
62  link = findByType(self.browser, ident, type)
63  except:
64  time.sleep(interval)
65  counter += interval
66  self.assertIsNotNone(link, "Cannot find link with ident='{css}' in {brow}".format(css=ident, brow='self.browser'))
67  link.first.click()
